Bahamas (AP) -- Hurricane Floyd strengthened to a very dangerous Category 4 storm today with 155 mph wind, surprising forecasters and charging toward the Bahamas on a path that also threatened the Florida coast.
Floyd had top sustained wind today of nearly 155 mph.
At 5 p.m.  Floyd was centered about 335 miles northeast of Puerto Rico's capital, San Juan.
